<subSubSection lastPageId="103" lastPageNumber="104" pageId="102" pageNumber="103" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="102.[151,1436,1856,2008]" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[208,336,1898,1924]" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body fusiform; gnathosoma large, abruptly curved and bent down near base; scapular setae (
<emphasis box="[161,185,1940,1965]" italics="true" pageId="102" pageNumber="103">sc</emphasis>
) present; genu II setae absent, femoral setae absent 
<taxonomicName box="[796,913,1940,1966]" form="both" pageId="102" pageNumber="103" rank="form">form both</taxonomicName>
legs, empodium entire; coxae I and coxae II each with 3 setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="103.[151,1436,158,226]" box="[208,1436,158,184]" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">
